embeds.title: FSD Beta Eligibility
embeds.description:
This was last updated 9/22/2022

To accepted into the beta at this time:

footer.text: Check @elonmusk's tweets for verification of info here....

fields.name: Software version
fields.value:
***You need to be on the 2022.20.xx branch.***
If you are on a newer version like, 2022.24 or 2022.28, you will need to wait for the beta branch to catch up to them before they will be accepted.(sorry)

NO, there is not a way to downgrade. It just wouldn't work.

Oh, you need FSD, purchased in full or subscribed, for it to work.

fields.name: Safety Score
fields.value: You need 80+ for your safety score **AND** atleast 100 miles on AP

fields.name: You must be in the US or Canada
Hardware
fields.value:
You need the Full-Self Driving Computer (AKA HW3) - Free upgrade w/ FSD package, or $1,000 for FSD Subscribers

If your legacy S/X was made before August 27th, 2017, you'll need a camera upgrade which will be available sometime in ~Oct.
